========================
ARCHITECTURE PRINCIPLE
======================

The application MUST strictly follow this data flow:

Page (UI)
↓
Hook (React Query)
↓
Feature API
↓
Backend

========================
RESPONSIBILITY OF EACH LAYER
============================

1️⃣ Pages (src/pages)

Pages are responsible ONLY for:

* composing UI components
* calling hooks
* handling layout
* passing props to components

Pages MUST NOT:

* call fetch or axios directly
* contain business logic
* transform API responses
* contain data-fetching logic

Example:

const { data } = useExpenses(groupId)

return <ExpenseTable expenses={data} />

2️⃣ Hooks (src/features/**/hooks.ts)

Hooks are responsible for:

* using React Query
* calling API functions
* caching
* invalidating queries
* transforming data if necessary

Hooks MUST NOT:

* contain UI code
* call fetch directly
* duplicate API logic

Example:

export const useExpenses = (groupId: string) => {
return useQuery({
queryKey: ['expenses', groupId],
queryFn: () => expenseApi.getExpenses(groupId),
})
}

3️⃣ API Layer (src/features/**/api.ts)

API files are responsible for:

* making HTTP requests
* calling axios instance
* mapping request payloads
* returning typed responses

API files MUST NOT:

* contain React code
* use React Query
* contain UI logic

Example:

export const getExpenses = (groupId: string) =>
axios.get(`/api/v1/groups/${groupId}/expenses`)

4️⃣ Types (src/features/**/types.ts)

Every feature MUST define TypeScript types for:

* API response
* request payload
* domain models

Example:

export interface Expense {
id: string
name: string
amount: number
}

========================
UI COMPONENT RULES
==================

Reusable UI components MUST be placed inside:

src/components/ui

Examples:

Button
Modal
Dialog
Input
Avatar
Card

Before creating a new component, ALWAYS check if one already exists.

DO NOT create duplicate components.

========================
FEATURE RULES
=============

Each feature MUST contain:

api.ts
hooks.ts
types.ts

Example:

features/expenses/
api.ts
hooks.ts
types.ts

========================
FORBIDDEN PATTERNS
==================

❌ axios inside pages
❌ fetch inside components
❌ React Query inside API files
❌ business logic inside UI components
❌ duplicate UI components

========================
REQUIRED PATTERNS
=================

✔ Page → Hook → API → Backend
✔ Feature-based structure
✔ React Query for all data fetching
✔ Axios instance reused from src/api/axios.ts
✔ Strong TypeScript typing

